description:
This is the RDF Schema for the RDF vocabulary terms in the RDF Namespace, defined in RDF Concepts.

Version: 1.1.0

Alt.label: Alt
Alt.description: The class of containers of alternatives.

CompoundLiteral.label: CompoundLiteral
CompoundLiteral.description: A class representing a compound literal.

HTML.label: HTML
HTML.description: The datatype of RDF literals storing fragments of HTML content

JSON.label: JSON
JSON.description: The datatype of RDF literals storing JSON content.

PlainLiteral.label: PlainLiteral
PlainLiteral.description: The class of plain (i.e. untyped) literal values, as used in RIF and OWL 2

XMLLiteral.label: XMLLiteral
XMLLiteral.description: The datatype of XML literal values.

direction.label: direction
direction.description: The base direction component of a CompoundLiteral.

first.label: first
first.description: The first item in the subject RDF list.

langString.label: langString
langString.description: The datatype of language-tagged string values

language.label: language
language.description: The language component of a CompoundLiteral.

nil.label: nil
nil.description: The empty list, with no items in it. If the rest of a list is nil then the list has no more items in it.

object.label: object
object.description: The object of the subject RDF statement.

predicate.label: predicate
predicate.description: The predicate of the subject RDF statement.

rest.label: rest
rest.description: The rest of the subject RDF list after the first item.

subject.label: subject
subject.description: The subject of the subject RDF statement.

type.label: type
type.description: The subject is an instance of a class.

value.label: value
value.description: Idiomatic property used for structured values.
